Package mainPack.jCustomClasses

Class JTestBench

java.lang.Object
mainPack.jCustomClasses.JTestBench
public class JTestBench extends Object
A class whose instatiations can be used for "Benchmark Testing", hence the name.

      public JTestBench()

    • JTestBench

      public JTestBench(long inSeed, JBloomType inBloomType, JGridSysType inGridSysType, JSkipListType inSkipListType, int inStartPower, int inEndPower, int inFailRate)
      A proper constructor for a JTestBench object instantiation.
      Parameters:
      inSeed - (long) Seed for the Random
      inBloomType - (JBloomType) Which Bloom Filter implementation to use
      inGridSysType - (JGridSysType) Which Coordinate System to use: GARS or MGRS
      inSkipListType - (JSkipListType) Which Skip List implementation to use
      inStartPowerOf10 - (int) Starting (i.e. smallest) size, in power of 10, of The Data Set and Test Set during the Test Bench run
      inEndPowerOf10 - (int) Ending (i.e. the largest) size, in power of 10, of The Data Set and Test Set during the Test Bench run

    • randFail

      public static boolean randFail(Random rng, double myFailRate)
      A CRUCIAL part of the .doCreate() method, enabling a specific fraction of The Data Set to be EXCLUDED from the Test Set.
      Parameters:
      rng - (Random) The initialized Random object passed around to allow a carefully curated set of random values, enabling repitiion of data sets
      myFailRate - (double) The probibalistic rate at which objects in The Data Set are excluded from the Test Set
      Returns:
      (boolean) A boolean vaule used to stochasticaly exclude data in The Data Set from the Test Set
